That's a fair enough idea, although in that case it would make sense to do something like put the null validation into a superclass and then ensure that all validations call through it. ex. (rough pseudojava):
abstract class SuperClass {
  void validate(String[] args) {
    doNullValidation(args);
    extraValidations(args);
  }
  void extraValidations(String[] args);
}

class SubClass {
  void extraValidations(String[] args) {
    doNumArgsValidation();
    doOtherValidations();
  }
}

A similar pattern can be found with the AbstractAuthenticatedRequestHandler, might be a good read to see how that handles everything.

